==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: malapert
<hw>mal"a*pert</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧l"⟦adot⟧*p⟦etil⟧rt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>malapert</ets> unskillful, ill-taught, ill-bred;
<ets>mal</ets> ill + <ets>apert</ets> open, adroit, intelligent, L.
<ets>apertus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>aperire</ets> to open. See
<er>Malice</er>, and <er>Aperient</er>.]</ety> <def>Bold; forward;
impudent; saucy; pert.</def> <au>Shak.</au> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>A malapert person.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Are you growing <qex>malapert</qex>! <qex>Will you force me to
make use of my authority</qex> ?</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mal"a*pert`ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>mal"a*pert`ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malapropism</ent>⟦br⟧
